<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8178314>
    dc:description "Fig. 16. Begonia heliantha Tebbitt. A. Habitat. B. Habit. C. Pistillate flower, oblique front view. D. Staminate and pistillate flower, front view (note, the pistillate flower is unusual in having four tepals and two styles). All photographs by J.P. Allen in Sandia Province, Puno Region." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8178314/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8178316>
    dc:description "Fig. 17. Distribution of Begonia sect. Australes L.B.Sm. & B.G.Schub. in Peru and surrounding countries. A. B. herrerae L.B.Sm. & B.G.Schub. (red) and B. heliantha Tebbitt (blue). B. B. veitchii Hook.f. var. veitchii (red) and B. veitchii var. machupicchuensis Tebbitt (red). Black lines indicate country borders, grey lines indicate major administrative divisions, blue lines indicate rivers, and shading indicates elevation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8178316/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

